Polish Regulator Clears Santander’s Takeover of Bank Zachodni

-- B y   D a v i d   M c Q u a i d
-- 
2011-02-18T14:22:05Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-18/polish-markets-regulator-approves-santander-s-takeover-of-bank-zachodni.html
  Banco Santander SA ,  Spain ’s biggest
bank, won the Polish regulator’s approval to buy a majority
stake in  Bank Zachodni WBK SA  from  Allied Irish Banks Plc ,
paving the way for its 16.6 billion-zloty ($5.7 billion) bid to
acquire 100 percent of the bank, the Warsaw-based Financial
Supervisory Commission said today in an e-mailed statement.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David McQuaid at 
 dmcquaid1@bloomberg.net  